{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778696236,"nonce":"wt57ipZrxSJre0lPRd5FgS+aTf4=","message":"**Not affected by the go-cue alignment fix (`06f7faf`).**\n\nThe primary Δv metric on this MVP is computed from peak forward velocity via `peak_v = jnp.max(jnp.where(after_go, v_fwd, -inf), axis=-1)` — per-trial after-go masking before `max`. The trial axis was never collapsed in absolute trial time, so the bug that affected `3702f54` / `f47abb1` / `2bc95fd` does not change the Δv numbers here. Verified by re-running `scripts/analyse_linear_decoupling_mvp.py` post-fix: all `peak_velocity_per_scale` values are bit-identical to the pre-fix `delta_v_summary.json`.\n\nThe forward-velocity profile *figure* under `results/410d7ac/figures/delta_v_signature/` was previously rendered with an absolute-time x-axis. It is now re-rendered with the x-axis recentred on the go cue (t=0) for visual accuracy.\n\nNote added to `results/410d7ac/notes/decoupling_acid_test_mvp.md` documenting that no quantitative correction is needed.\n\nCross-ref: commits `53362d9` / `0e14755` / `c7a7883` / `35769d1` on `feature/go-cue-alignment-fix`.","files":null}]}